  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "When we request a block by root, we get the block and mark the block as seen when we insert the block to the pending queue\r\n```go\r\nfunc (s *Service) insertBlockToPendingQueue(_ primitives.Slot, b interfaces.ReadOnlySignedBeaconBlock, r [32]byte) error {\r\n\tif s.seenPendingBlocks[r] {\r\n\t\treturn nil\r\n\t}\r\n\tif err := s.addPendingBlockToCache(b); err != nil {\r\n\t\treturn err\r\n\t}\r\n\ts.seenPendingBlocks[r] = true\r\n\treturn nil\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nOnce we `seenPendingBlocks[r]` is true, we'll never be able to request the same block by root again\r\n```go\r\nfunc (s *Service) sendBatchRootRequest(ctx context.Context, roots [][32]byte, randGen *rand.Rand) error {\r\n\tfor i := len(roots) - 1; i >= 0; i-- {\r\n\t\tr := roots[i]\r\n\t\tif s.seenPendingBlocks[r] || s.cfg.chain.BlockBeingSynced(r) {\r\n\t\t\troots = append(roots[:i], roots[i+1:]...)\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow, you can imagine a block with one blob that you are asking for. You cycle through your peers. The first peer you request returns a block with a bad blob. But you will never try to make a second request. Your node is officially stuck until a restart",
